# PS4 Baikal Kernel 6.x Patch Series
#
# Apply order: low number first. Within a directory, files apply
# alphabetically (0001-..., 0002-..., etc.).
#
# Source:
#   - Bulk patches extracted from crashniels/linux ps4-linux-6.15.y-baikal
#     (HEAD b3b6b1e4f) on top of vanilla v6.15.4 (e60eb4415).
#     crashniels has already done the heavy 5.4 → 6.15 forward-port,
#     including Liverpool support in radeon, amdkfd quirks, the MSI
#     subsystem refactor, and the iommu directory move.
#   - feeRnt's xhci-aeolia Baikal shutdown fix
#     (b0969f7d101f, on x_exp__6.15.4-baikal-crashniels).
#   - One local fix for the bpcie-icc void-pointer bug.
#
# Notable gaps vs the 5.4-baikal stack:
#   - MT7668 (mt76x8) vendor WiFi/BT driver is NOT yet ported. Boot the
#     kernel without WiFi first; mt7668 is tracked in 9000-todo/.
#
# Generator: scripts/generate-6.x-patches.sh
#
# To temporarily disable a patch, comment its line.

# === 0100: x86 platform (Kconfig, head64, bootparam, PS4 init, TSC calib)
0100-x86-platform/0001-x86-add-ps4-platform-support.patch
# v40: THE ACTUAL ROOT CAUSE FIX for 6.x HDMI. PS4 has null_legacy_pic
# so early_irq_init allocates 0 legacy descs. ACPI request_irq(9, ...)
# for SCI fails (-EINVAL) because irq_to_desc(9)=NULL. Cascade:
# SCI install fails -> acpi_terminate -> mutex delete -> ATOM BIOS
# returns 0 -> amdgpu PLL garbage -> blank HDMI.
# Pre-allocate IRQ 9 desc with dummy_irq_chip in arch_initcall.
0100-x86-platform/0002-x86-ps4-allocate-irq9-desc-for-acpi-sci.patch

# === 0150: ACPI OSL fixes (PS4-specific)
# v35: Revert SCI install from request_threaded_irq to request_irq.
# This is the ROOT CAUSE of the HDMI display being broken in 6.x.
# 6.x's IRQF_ONESHOT shared-add gets rejected on PS4 IRQ9 -> ACPI mutex
# init incomplete -> ATOM BIOS broken -> amdgpu PLL programming dead.
0150-acpi/0001-acpi-osl-ps4-revert-sci-to-request-irq.patch

