# v56 falsified v54/source-training as the lane-lock killer: with 0028 disabled,
# post-modeset chunk A still timed out (~607 ms) and 0x60f8 still dropped from
# 0xff to 0x0f. The remaining v53-added source-side state changes are TX SETUP
# and SETUP_VSEMPH immediately before TX ENABLE. For v57, remove only these two
# injected ATOM transmitter actions and return to DISABLE -> ENABLE so we can
# test whether SETUP/VSEMPH disturb the BIOS-default locked bridge link.
# 0300-gpu-liverpool/0027-amdgpu-ps4-tx-setup-vsemph-before-enable.patch
# v54 (2026-05-10): source-only DP training pulse. DISABLED for v56.
# v55 chunk-split evidence showed the bridge starts with DP receiver lane lock
# intact (0x60f8=0xff, chunk A completes in ~31 ms) during the force-init cycle,
# then loses it after the GPU modeset path and this TPS1/TPS2/COMPLETE pulse
# (0x60f8=0x0f, chunk A times out in ~605 ms). For v56, revert only this pulse
# to test whether it is the step that destroys the BIOS-default locked link.
# 0300-gpu-liverpool/0028-amdgpu-ps4-source-only-dp-training-pulse.patch
