# instrumentation: trace cq_wait_set/wait_clear enqueue, time and dump
# every cq_exec (elapsed_us + reply.res1/res2/count + databuf[0..7]),
# and split the MN864729 main seq into 3 chunks at wait boundaries
# (Chunk A = DP lane status 0x60f8/0x60f9, Chunk B = HDMI update 0x10f6,
# Chunk C = PLL 0x7204) with cq_read readbacks of polled registers
# between. Identifies which exact wait fires the timeout in one boot.
0300-gpu-liverpool/0029-amdgpu-ps4-bridge-cq-instrumentation-chunk-split.patch
# v58 (2026-05-10): step-by-step DP lane-status probe. Adds
# ps4_bridge_probe_lane_status helper in ps4_bridge.c that reads
# 0x60f8/0x60f9 via the bridge ICC queue. Calls inserted in
# atombios_crtc.c (before/after AdjustDisplayPll, after SetPixelClock)
# and atombios_encoders.c (after each dig_encoder action, before+after
# each dig_tx action). The first probe where 0x60f8 flips from 0xff to
# 0x0f identifies the exact modeset step destroying the inherited DP
# RX lock. ~10 calls x ~10ms = ~100ms overhead during modeset. Pure
# read-only diagnostic.
0300-gpu-liverpool/0030-amdgpu-ps4-step-by-step-lane-status-probe.patch
# v59 (2026-05-10): TARGETED FIX. v58 trace identified TX DISABLE as the
# singular killer of the BIOS-trained DP link (0x60f8: 0xff -> 0x9f
# exactly at action=0). Subsequent TX ENABLE doesn't restore the lock.
# Skip ATOM_TRANSMITTER_ACTION_DISABLE in setup_dig's ATOM_DISABLE branch
# for Liverpool/Gladius DP encoders. The firmware-trained PHY stays
# powered through modeset; later TX ENABLE fires on an already-enabled
# PHY. Logs "preserving PS4 DP TX lock; skip TX DISABLE" when the gate
# fires. Other DPMS_OFF operations (DP_VIDEO_OFF, dp_set_rx_power_state)
# are NOT skipped — v58 confirmed they preserve f8=0xff.
0300-gpu-liverpool/0031-amdgpu-ps4-skip-tx-disable-preserve-firmware-dp-lock.patch
# v60 (2026-05-10): v59 trace confirmed both halves of the TX DISABLE/ENABLE
# pair are destructive. Skipping DISABLE preserved f8=0xff through
# DP_VIDEO_OFF + DIG SETUP/PANEL_MODE, but TX ENABLE then flipped f8 from
# 0xff -> 0x0f (more destructive than DISABLE was, which had flipped to
# 0x9f). Extend v59's preserve-firmware-state model: also gate ATOM_
# TRANSMITTER_ACTION_ENABLE in setup_dig's ATOM_ENABLE branch. Leaves
# the firmware-trained PHY completely untouched. DP_VIDEO_ON is the
# remaining unknown — its effect on an intact lock is tested for the
# first time in v60.
0300-gpu-liverpool/0032-amdgpu-ps4-skip-tx-enable-too.patch

